Let \[f(x) =
\begin{cases}
3x + 5 &\text{if }x<-3, \\
7-4x&\text{if }x\ge -3.
\end{cases}
\]Find $f(5)$.

Rationale:
We have the equation $\frac{3+x}{5+x}=\frac{1+x}{2+x}$. Simplifying, we get \begin{align*}
(3+x)(2+x)&=(5+x)(1+x)\\
6+5x+x^2&=5+6x+x^2\\
x&=\boxed{1}.
\end{align*}

