label("$15$", (A + C)/2, NE);
label("$10$", (A + M)/2, SW);
label("$10$", (D + M)/2, SW);
label("$7$", (C + D)/2, E);
[/asy]

The semi-perimeter of triangle $ACD$ is $(7 + 15 + 20)/2 = 21$, so by Heron's formula, the area of triangle $ACD$ is $$\sqrt{21 (21 - 7)(21 - 15)(21 - 20)} = \boxed{42}.$$

Problem:
In the diagram, the area of triangle $ABC$ is 27 square units. What is the area of triangle $BCD$?

[asy]

draw((0,0)--(32,0)--(9,15)--(0,0));

dot((0,0));
label("$A$",(0,0),SW);
label("6",(3,0),S);
dot((6,0));
label("$C$",(6,0),S);
label("26",(19,0),S);
dot((32,0));
label("$D$",(32,0),SE);
dot((9,15));
