label("$24$",Y/2,S);

[/asy]

The Pythagorean Theorem gives us $XZ= \sqrt{YZ^2 - XY^2} = \sqrt{625-576} = \sqrt{49}=7$, so $\tan Y = \frac{XZ}{XY} = \ \boxed{\frac{7}{24}}$.

